# Upstox Node.js SDK - Project Structure Guide

This is the official Upstox Node.js SDK for communicating with the Upstox API v2. The SDK is auto-generated using Swagger Codegen and follows specific architectural patterns.

## Core Architecture

The main entry point is [src/index.js](mdc:src/index.js), which exports all API classes, models, and feeder functions. The built distribution is in [dist/](mdc:dist/) and mirrors the [src/](mdc:src/) structure.

## Key Directories

- **[src/api/](mdc:src/api/)** - Contains all API endpoint classes (OrderApi, MarketQuoteApi, etc.)
- **[src/model/](mdc:src/model/)** - Contains all data model classes for requests/responses
- **[src/feeder/](mdc:src/feeder/)** - WebSocket streaming functionality (MarketDataStreamer, PortfolioDataStreamer)
- **[src/feeder/proto/](mdc:src/feeder/proto/)** - Protocol buffer definitions for WebSocket feeds
- **[test/](mdc:test/)** - Test files mirroring the src structure
- **[examples/](mdc:examples/)** - Usage examples including WebSocket implementations
- **[docs/](mdc:docs/)** - Auto-generated API documentation

## Build System

The project uses Babel for transpilation. The build script in [package.json](mdc:package.json) compiles ES6 modules from `src/` to `dist/` and copies `.proto` files. The main entry point for consumers is `dist/index.js`.

## API Client Pattern

All API classes extend from [ApiClient](mdc:src/ApiClient.js) which handles:
- Authentication (OAuth2)
- Request/response serialization
- Sandbox mode support
- Different base URLs for order operations vs other APIs

## Naming Conventions

- API classes: `{Domain}Api` (e.g., OrderApi, MarketQuoteApi)
- Model classes: PascalCase descriptive names (e.g., PlaceOrderRequest, GetOrderResponse)
- Feeder classes: `{Type}DataStreamer` (e.g., MarketDataStreamer, PortfolioDataStreamer)